language ESSENCE' 1.0

letting v be 3
letting k be 2
letting l be 1
letting b be (l*v*(v-1))/(k*(k-1))
letting r be (l*(v-1))/(k-1)

find  bibd: matrix indexed by [int(1..3), int(1..3)] of int(0..1)


such that
  $ each block contains k different objects 
  forAll block : int(1..3) .
    (sum object : int(1..3).  bibd[object, block]) =  k,

  $ each object occurs in r blocks
  forAll object : int(1..3) .
    (sum block : int(1..3). bibd[object, block]) = r ,

  $ two different objects occurr in a block exactly l times
  forAll object1 : int(1..3) .
    forAll object2 : int(1..3) .
      (object1 < object2) ->  
      ((sum block : int(1..3). 
        bibd[object1,block] * bibd[object2, block]) = l),

  $ Some symmetry breaking constraints
  forAll row: int(1..2) .
    bibd[row,..] <=lex bibd[row+1,..],

  forAll col: int(1..2) .
    bibd[..,col] <=lex bibd[..,col+1]
